notesStmt.note: Title for manuscripts from title of first work (f. 1r).

msContents.summary: Copies of material related to Giulio Sacchetti's diplomatic trip to Spain, on behalf of Pope Urban VIII, to persuade Philip IV of Spain to reach an agreement with Louis XIII of France about the passage of Valtellina in the Lombard region, which the French invaded in 1624.
msContents.textLang: Italian, with sections in Latin and Spanish

msItem.title: Alcune note de negotii per Spagna, f. 31r
Ristretto di quanto a bocca mi e stato accennare da Mons. Magalotti per conto di Spagna, f. 38r
Ristretto contenuto nella consuloa data in Spagna..., f. 47r
Note cavate dalle lettere del Nuncio Castagna, f. 55r
Ristretto della capitolatione [per la Valtellina], f. 64v
Lettere del re e ministri, f. 153r

supportDesc.extent: 279 leaves : 263 x 190 (226 x 133) mm. bound to 273 x 195 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 279 + i (contemporary paper); [1-279]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

binding.p: Contemporary vellum. Oxidation of ink has resulted in some loss of text (f. 1) and general discoloration and brittle paper throughout. Evidence of worm damage near binding.

origin.p: Written in Italy after 1626 (latest date in manuscript, f. 206r).

history.provenance: Bequest of Francis Campbell Macauley, 1896 (bookplate, Macauley Library, University of Pennsylvania, inside upper cover).
